criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

          -  DSM-IV Major Depressive Episode (as part of a Major Depressive Disorder or  Bipolar
             Disorder), of minimum 4 weeks duration.

          -  MADRS score ≥ 20 at study entry.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  DSM-IV psychotic disorder;

          -  drug or alcohol abuse or dependence (preceding 12 months);

          -  inadequate response to ECT (current episode of depression);

          -  anticonvulsant or benzodiazepine medication;

          -  rapid clinical response required, e.g. high suicide risk; clinically defined
             neurological disorder or insult;

          -  metal in the cranium, skull defects, or skin lesions on scalp (cuts, abrasions, rash)
             at proposed electrode sites;

          -  pregnancy.
